# Example env file for the cloud/ scripts.
#
# Copy this to cloud/.env (already gitignored) and fill in the values.
# Then:   set -a; source cloud/.env; set +a   (exports vars into your shell)
# Or:     use 'env $(grep -v "^#" cloud/.env | xargs)' as a prefix.
#
# None of these values are permanent — FASTMRI_URL is a time-limited
# secret, and the others are here only to document the defaults the
# scripts bake in.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# FASTMRI_URL — presigned S3 URL for a single fastMRI archive.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Where this comes from:
#   1. Register + sign the data-use agreement at https://fastmri.med.nyu.edu.
#   2. You'll get an email titled "fastMRI Data Access" with a long block
#      of curl commands, one per dataset file. Each command looks like:
#
#          curl -C - "https://fastmri-dataset.s3.amazonaws.com/v2.0/brain_multicoil_val_batch_0.tar.xz?AWSAccessKeyId=...&Signature=...&Expires=..." \
#               --output brain_multicoil_val_batch_0.tar.xz
#
#   3. Copy the URL between the quotes (everything from https:// up to
#      the closing quote). That whole string, including the query
#      parameters, is what this variable holds.
#
# Important:
#   - The URL is a credential. Do not paste it into Slack, PRs, issues,
#     public docs, or commit messages. Keep it in cloud/.env only.
#   - It expires. The Expires=<unix-timestamp> query parameter tells you
#     when — typically ~30 days after issue. Re-request from NYU if yours
#     has lapsed.
#   - Each URL is specific to one file. To pull additional batches,
#     overwrite this value and re-run the upload script.
FASTMRI_URL='https://fastmri-dataset.s3.amazonaws.com/v2.0/brain_multicoil_val_batch_0.tar.xz?AWSAccessKeyId=REPLACE&Signature=REPLACE&Expires=REPLACE'

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional overrides — the scripts default to these values, only set
# them here if you're deviating (e.g. running against a different
# project or bucket).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# PROJECT=fastmri-493921
# BUCKET=fastmri-493921-brain-val
# REGION=us-central1
# LIFECYCLE_CUSTOM_TIME=2026-06-12
# LIFECYCLE_DAYS_AFTER=90

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# How to run the upload once this file is filled in
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# From the repo root:
#
#     set -a; source cloud/.env; set +a
#     ./cloud/upload_from_nyu.sh "$FASTMRI_URL" brain_multicoil_val_batch_0.tar.xz
#
# The script streams the URL straight to gs://$BUCKET/<object> without
# writing to local disk, and stamps the object with the lifecycle
# customTime so auto-deletion lands on the intended date.
#
# For additional batches, replace FASTMRI_URL with the batch_1 / batch_2
# URL from the same email and re-run with the corresponding object name.
